<article id="node-16983">
<h1 >3.4.6.60 Notification &amp; Recipient Obligations for SpNP</h1>
<h2>Notifiable events for <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#spNP" title="Special needs pension">SpNP</a></h2>
<p>In addition to the common notifiable events, SpNP recipients must notify Centrelink within the 14-day notification period, if they return to Australia. The notification and recipient obligations for SpNP recipients otherwise are the same as those applying to the payment they would otherwise qualify for.</p>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> A special needs age pensioner has the same obligations as other <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#age" title="Age pension">Age</a> pensioners.</p>
</div>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/4/1/50">3.4.1.50</a> Notification &amp; Recipient Obligations for Age, <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/4/2/40">3.4.2.40</a> Notification &amp; Recipient Obligations for WP, <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/4/4/70">3.4.4.70</a> Notification &amp; Recipient Obligations for WidB, <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/6/1/90">3.6.1.90</a> Notification &amp; Recipient Obligations for DSP</p>
</div>
<h2>Comparable foreign payment (<a href="http://guides.dss.gov.au/guide-social-security-law/1/1/c/230">1.1.C.230</a>)</h2>
<p>The Secretary of the Department may require a recipient or their partner, to take reasonable action to obtain a <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#cfp" title="Comparable foreign payment">CFP</a>, if:</p>
<ul><li>the recipient is likely to be entitled to a payment from a CFP country, AND</li>
<li>has not applied for the payment.</li>
</ul><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A00580" title="Social Security (Administration) Act 1999">SS(Admin)Act</a> section 66 Notice to obtain foreign payment, section 40 Rejection of claim for failure to obtain foreign payment</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../guide-social-security-law/7/1">7.1</a> Conditions for Payment Outside Australia, <a href="../guide-social-security-law/7/2">7.2</a> Arrangements for Payment Outside Australia, <a href="../guide-social-security-law/7/3/1/20">7.3.1.20</a> Reasonable Action Requirements</p>
</div>
<h2>Common provisions</h2>
<p>Some notification and recipient obligations are common to MOST payments.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/1/3">3.1.3</a> Notification &amp; Recipient Obligations</p>
</div>
